         </P><P> Like this :<BR>Essentially, the wizard gets to do his damage 'first' and the necro gets to do his damage 'last', what needs to be avoided is the necro reaching his potential (being almost as good as the wizard) happen next to none. There's ways to do this. Dots that start their damage strong (Reverse splurt) and fade away are a good idea. These are tuned by the ability to NOT overwrite your own dot (hence reapplying the strong segment) and being incredibly effecient. Give necros a host of these dots, vs varying resists and to different degrees. It's the same as giving wizards various ratio nukes - they have to decide which to use based on fight length. For long fights, run with the splurt idea, it's a VERY GOOD IDEA. Make 10 minute 'splurts' that are DEVASTATING once they reach their 8 min+ mark. Make very long duration 'fire and forget' spells that can be depended on to sustain 10 dps for a long long fight without having to reapply (the essence of effeciency).</P><P></P><P>Sennen De`Sade<BR>54 DE Heretic<BR>Drinal<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
